[emph]Sub Modules[/emph]

For show all the availables submodules, the indexcontroller return a var "submodules".
This var contains the result of the _getSubmodules() function.
By default, the _getSubmodules calls the Phprojekt_SubModules, that read all the CORE_PATH
and return all the folders, except the system´s folders like:

'Administration', 'Groups', 'Phprojekt', 'Role', 'Users',

and the CVS´s folders like:

'.','..','.cvsignore','CVS'.

All the other folder, are modules for show.

In each IndexController of each module, you can rewrite the _getSubmodules() function,
for work it with rights or other special stuff if you want.

The submodules var is just an array, that are transformed in the index.phtml to:
"{'Default,'History,'Note,'Project,'Todo'}"
The client will show all these submodules and knows which are the current one.